added.title: Booty Eggs
added.description: Not wanting to be creeped out on Easter the Titans dispatch the Easter Bunny and take matters into their own hands.

added.title: TV Knight 4
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon go camping but instead of fun outdoor activities they'd rather watch TV.

added.title: Cartoon Feud
added.description: Control Freak forces the Titans and the Scooby Gang to compete on Family Feud.

added.title: TV Knight 5
added.description: Batman pretends to be sick to avoid work so he and Commissioner Gordon can run around town watching their favorite shows.

added.title: Teen Titans Vroom: Part 1
added.description: In this episode of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans gain the ability to transform into cars.

added.title: Teen Titans Vroom: Part 2
added.description: In the exciting conclusion of "Turbo Titans Go Force" the Titans must learn to work together to stop Dr. Military.

added.title: TV Knight
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon check in on various happenings around Jump City.

added.title: Easter Creeps
added.description: It's Easter and the Tooth Fairy is trying to take over the holiday.

added.title: TV Knight 2
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon have a slumber party and watch their favorite TV shows.

added.title: TV Knight 3
added.description: Batman is more interested in watching TV than participating in his birthday party.

added.title: The Teen Titans Go Easter Holiday Classic
added.description: The Easter Bunny is missing, and it's up to the Titans to find him before Easter is ruined.

added.title: Batman vs. Teen Titans: Dark Injustice
added.description: The Titans try to outprank each other on April Fools' Day.

added.title: And the Award for Sound Design Goes to Rob
added.description: Raven just wants some piece and quiet for once, and accidentally makes a magical deal that eliminates all sounds.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Rocknaldo
added.description: Ronaldo sets out to find all the rock people living in Beach City!

added.title: Doug Out
added.description: Steven and Connie join Connie's father on a stake out.

added.title: Too Short to Ride
added.description: Steven and Amethyst take a trip to Funland but run into trouble when their friend is too short to ride the rollercoasters.

added.title: Gem Hunt
added.description: Steven and Connie track a Gem monster through the wilderness but its tracks lead them to mystery.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Friend Ship
added.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

added.title: Together Breakfast
added.description: Steven tries to get the Gems to take part in his special breakfast tradition, but instead finds himself tumbling through the magical catacombs of the Crystal Gem's temple.

added.title: Tiger Millionaire
added.description: Steven joins Amethyst in an underground wrestling league.

added.title: Lion 2: The Movie
added.description: Steven and Connie try to ride the Lion to the movie theater but Lion has other ideas.

added.title: Full Disclosure
added.description: Steven tries to avoid Connie so he doesn't have to tell her about his most recent harrowing adventure.

added.title: Open Book
added.description: Steven and Connie want a new ending to a beloved book series, so Steven takes them into Rose's Room to re-enact it.

added.title: Joy Ride
added.description: The Cool Kids help Steven put some fun back in his life.

added.title: The Father
added.description: When Frankie attends a party at The Watterson's he realizes it's a holiday Granny Jojo made up to celebrate the day he left. Richard is feeling sad about the years he lost with Frankie so the kids try anything to cheer him up.

added.title: The Cringe
added.description: When the uncomfortableness between them reaches new levels, Gumball and Hot Dog Guy decide they have to confront their ongoing awkwardness by making things as awkward as possible.

added.title: The Cage
added.description: When Mr. Corneille shows up to work with a mysterious bruise, Gumball and Darwin discover that he's teacher by day and a cage fighter by night, or was until he vowed never to fight again. However, when the school is being closed for a lack of finances the boys have to try and convince him to come out retirement for one last fight.

added.title: The Faith
added.description: Everything in Elmore is suddenly just various shades of grey, and things all over town are going wrong. Gumball and Darwin follow the mayhem and learn that one person was holding the whole town together: Alan. They have to restore his faith in the world to bring color back to Elmore.

added.title: The Choices
added.description: When a typically stressful Watterson family dinner pushes her to the edge of her sanity, Nicole starts reminiscing about the time she met Richard. Might her life have been better if she'd never stopped to talk to her future husband and taken a different path instead?

added.title: The Crew
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin decide it's time they join a crew, they agree that the coolest posse in Elmore is the Senior Citizens. They do everything they can to fit in with them, going to extraordinary lengths to prove themselves worthy of running (well, walking very slowly) with them.

added.title: The Awkwardness
added.description: Gumball is walking in the same direction as Hot Dog Guy, and with each step it becomes increasingly awkward.

added.title: The Blame
added.description: Gumball gives Billy his first taste of videogames but the sheer excitement causes him to pass out. His mother Felicity summons the PTA and threatens to ban video games all across Elmore. Gumball and Darwin are given three chances to prove that videogames can be a force for good. But when they fail, they decide to prove books can be just as dangerous.

added.title: The Allergy
added.description: Gumball needs to find a cure for Darwin's allergy before he sneezes Elmore off the map. Darwin starts sneezing repeatedly and it seems he can't stop. The Wattersons figure maybe he's allergic to something. After a few guesses, they come to the conclusion that he is allergic to stupidity. Being surrounded by stupid people, this is something of a problem. And they need to find a solution before Darwin's increasingly explosive sneezes destroy the town.

added.title: The Downer
added.description: Gumball is in a funk that is proving hard to shake. Gumball refuses to get out of bed because he is in a lousy mood. When his family try to cheer him up Gumball wishes they'd all just disappear and, inexplicably, they do. At first he enjoys the solitude and doing just as he pleases but soon his mood threatens to take control of him completely.

added.title: The Boombox
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to understand Juke's urgent Beatbox message, but why won't he just speak English?!!

added.title: The DVD
added.description: Gumball is desperate to avoid a late fee on the rented dvd he accidentally destroyed.

added.title: The End
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are convinced that the world will end in 24 hours.

added.title: The Prank
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's harmless pranks on Dad spiral hopelessly out of control.

added.title: The Club
added.description: When Gumball rejects "The Rejects Club", the rejects wreak their revenge.

added.title: The Unfinished Car
added.description: The gang enters an unfinished train car and tries to fix it.

added.title: The Chrome Car
added.description: The gang meets a familiar face in a mirrored car.

added.title: The Ball Pit Car
added.description: The gang is confronted by a strange new force on a Ball Pit Car adventure.

added.title: The Past Car
added.description: Tulip takes a risk trusting an old foe.

added.title: The Engine
added.description: Tulip makes it to the front of the train and is faced with a choice.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Vic loses a wrestling match, V&V journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: Pool Duel
added.description: Unikitty and the gang are having a great time at the public pool, until they try to get Puppycorn to swim in the deep end with them. Puppycorn is terrified of the deep end. Now Unikitty and the gang must get him over his fear, so he can have maximum pool fun. Meanwhile, Master Frown and Brock are hatching a plan to ruin everyone's fun, by pulling the pool's plug.

added.title: This Spells Disaster
added.description: The gang is planning a surprise for Puppycorn, so they spell things out when talking so he won't find out. Desperate to know what they're saying, Puppycorn finds a magic book that he thinks will help him learn to spell, but unbeknownst to him, it's teaching him how to cast spells! Will Puppycorn realize that knowledge is power and some secrets are kept for a reason?

added.title: Kitty & Hawk
added.description: When Puppycorn's favorite toy goes missing, Unikitty & Hawkodile team up to track down the thief, buddy-cop style! But when things get tough and the case goes cold, now it's not just their partnership on the line, but their friendship!

added.title: Perfect Moment
added.description: When Hawkodile admits his love for Dr. Fox, Unikitty and the gang become his love gurus to help him confess his feelings for her. Unfortunately, Unikitty's grand plans for the perfect moment of love complicates everything.

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device
added.description: When boredom levels in the castle hit dangerously high levels, Dr. Fox conveniently introduces her P.L.O.T. Device. When pressed, this device alters reality to make it more exciting. Richard warns that this might be dangerous, but no one listens. It's not long till he is proven correct and life in the castle becomes dangerously exciting.

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: Action Forest
added.description: Hawkodile is the toughest action hero in the land, until his old rival shows up to take vengeance on him. Defeated and in need of help, Hawkodile must train Unikitty and the others into super muscle­y tough bros. And there's only one place unstoppable warriors are made, the Action Forest.

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Kitchen Chaos
added.description: After a workplace injury, Richard is unable to do his servant work. Unikitty and the others take on the task of one simple chore, clean the kitchen. This incredibly boring task taxes our heroes as they find every way possible to not do it. Will they be able to accomplish this goal and bring Richard back?

added.title: Christmas Movies
added.description: On Christmas Eve, the Baby Bears defend a video store from getting robbed.

added.title: Imaginary Friend
added.description: The Baby Bears invent an imaginary friend, but the trouble he causes is all too real.

added.title: Tunnels
added.description: The Bears discover a network of tunnels underneath the cave. Are they prepared to discover where they lead to and who dug them?

added.title: Ramen
added.description: The Baby Bears help a struggling ramen chef perfect her ramen and save her shop.

added.title: The Audition
added.description: The Bears audition to be the next mascot for their favorite cereal. They get so caught up in the process that their competitiveness gets the best of them.

added.title: Captain Craboo
added.description: The Bears are reunited with their pet crab, Captain Craboo. But after an unfortunate run-in with Nom Nom, the Bears may lose their pet forever.

added.title: Baby Bears on a Plane
added.description: The Baby Bears have an adventure in the sky while aboard a plane to Sweden. But when the baby Bears are forced to sit in different sections of the plan, things get a bit haywire for everyone on board.

added.title: Yuri and the Bear
added.description: Baby Ice Bear lives alone in the arctic and meets a mysterious man named Yuri. Together they help each other survive the cold environment.

added.title: Grizz Helps
added.description: When his brothers don't need his help for the day, Grizz leaves the cave to assist anyone he can throughout the city.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val le guarda rencor a Vic, lo cual atrae sin querer a un malvado cadejo, una bestia mitológica parecida a un lobo.

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 1
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 2
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Planet X
added.description: When Rad returns to his home planet, he learns a shocking truth about alien society.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: Carl
added.description: A pleasant weekend goes awry when a monster attacks.

added.title: Lord Cowboy Darrell
added.description: Everyone is forced to deal with some major changes at Boxmore.

added.title: Beach Episode
added.description: Surf's up on a wacky beach adventure when our heroes are challenged to the ultimate beach battle.

added.title: OK A.U.!
added.description: An evil warlock takes our heroes to a strange alternate universe.

added.title: KO's Health Week
added.description: KO spends a week dispensing healthy tips to everyone in the plaza.

added.title: Dark Plaza
added.description: KO and the heroes of the Plaza fight to save Lakewood Plaza Turbo with everything on the line.

added.title: One Last Score
added.description: KO decides to help Ginger recapture her glory days.

added.title: T.K.O.
added.description: Searching for power, KO accepts the help of a mysterious figure. Our heroes band together to save the plaza from a new menace.

added.title: The Power Is Yours!
added.description: A special hero helps Lakewood Plaza Turbo save the planet.

added.title: Plazalympics
added.description: KO takes part in Lakewood Plaza Turbo's annual Plazalympics competition.

added.title: Parents Day
added.description: It's Parents' Day at Lakewood Plaza Turbo!

added.title: RMS & Brandon's First Episode
added.description: A Real Magic Skeleton discovers a new job opportunity.

added.title: Ice Cream Headache
added.description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

added.title: Pepper's Blanket Is Missing
added.description: Pepper's blanket goes missing at a cabin sleepover.

added.title: Hedgehog Werewolf
added.description: Hedgehog gets bit by a cute puppy and is starting to act strange.

added.title: Mr. Softball
added.description: Susie challenges the campers to a game of softball to get out of doing a chore.

added.title: Fuzzy Pink Time Babies
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn how to stop time.

added.title: Finn the Human
added.description: After chasing the Lich through the portal, Finn and Jake meet a wishmaster named Prismo.

added.title: Jake the Dog
added.description: Jake and Prismo watch from the portal as the Ice King's crown makes Finn more and more powerful.

added.title: Benson's Car
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix Benson's car before he finds out they broke its window.

added.title: A Skips in Time
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Skips return Teenage Skips to the 1700s.

added.title: The Boys Are Back in Town
added.description: Him brings the Rowdyruff Boys back, protecting them from the girls' feminine wiles.

added.title: Bad Portrait
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to re-paint Benson's portrait for a party.

added.title: Catching the Wave
added.description: Pops wants to catch a wave.

added.title: Bachelor Party! Zingo!
added.description: Skips must plan the perfect bachelor party for his cousin, Quips.

added.title: Sons of Mars
added.description: A case of Martian mistaken identity comes to Ooo when Magic Man turns Jake into a copy of himself.

added.title: I Remember You
added.description: Ice King and Marceline share a tender - and revealing - few moments reminiscing.

added.title: The Lich
added.description: A visit from the Lich King shines some light on some of Ooo's secrets in this season finale cliffhanger.

added.title: Midnight Madness
added.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

added.title: Worship
added.description: When the Fashionistas unveil their new mind controlling perfume, the Powerpuff Girls must find a way to stop them before Townsville falls under their spell.

added.title: Ballroom
added.description: MG fixes up the ballroom and warns UG and PS not to step a foot in there until he gets a chance to use it.  But UG mistakenly tosses a ball into the room.  Now PS and UG have to retrieve the ball without touching one foot to the ground.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Space Oddity
added.description: In the year 3021, the gang's intergalactic mission goes awry when a strange alien creature infiltrates their ship.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Small World: Abra-Disaster Part 1
added.description: After defeating Mojo for the umpteenth time, the Powerpuff Girls are confident they are unstoppable.

added.title: Bucketboy!
added.description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: A crash landing sends Townsville over the edge.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Numbskull
added.description: A head Injury turns Mr. Gus into a bumbling fools whose wacky antics make him Uncle Grandpa's coolest friend. No longer the focus of Uncle Grandpa's attention, a jealous Pizza Steve tries to desperately to get back normal. Mr. Gus has to restore social balance in the RV.

added.title: The Package
added.description: The gang gets nutty after repeatedly failing to open a mysterious package.

added.title: Pachydermus Packard and the Camp of Fantasy
added.description: A doctor orders Mr. Pachydermus to have an adventure, so he attends the Warriors' super-annoying, "Fantasy Camp"!

added.title: Let's Team Up Because We Aren't Bad Friends
added.description: The Warriors fear that they've been ignoring their pals, so they team up with Witchy Simone and Noville for a BIG MISSION, only to discover that their friends aren't into it anymore.

added.title: Case Clothed
added.description: Princess Zange hires the Warriors to be her secret service for the afternoon to go shopping, but the looting pirates of Keelhaul Cove make fashion makeovers nearly impossible to manage.

added.title: Nuclear Family Values
added.description: Firestorm encounters the Nuclear Family, a misguided group of robots who resemble a '50's sitcom family. They intend on blowing up a nuclear power plant in order to create a home where no one can touch them and they hope to use Firestorm's power to help them.

added.title: Cleanliness Is Next to Grupliness
added.description: Grup has been stinking up the entire town of Rhyboflaven, but no matter how the Warriors try to lead the little dragon to water, they can't make him bathe!

added.title: The Rowdy Ruff Boys
added.description: Mojo Jojo creates the ultimate weapons against the Powerpuff Girls, boy equivalents! Enter Butch, Boomer and Brick, The Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Gotta Get Grup to Get Down
added.description: Grup hires the Warriors to help him become the biggest music star in Rhyboflaven, yet helping the little dragon achieve his big dream is no small task.

added.title: Locked Out
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

added.title: Uh, Oh, Dynamo
added.description: Worried about his little girls' safety, the Professor creates Powerpuff Dynamo, a state-of-the-art protection system, to help them in battle.

added.title: Plastic Man Saves the World
added.description: Plastic Man feels shuffled off to the side as the Justice League battles Brainiac so he takes it upon himself to infiltrate the alien's ship on his own and thwart the villain's plans.

added.title: Average Jeff
added.description: Jeff suffers an identity crisis when a standardized test lands him in the lesser of the classes academic groupings.

added.title: Belson's Sleepover
added.description: Belson invites Clarence and friends to a sleepover party, with a catch: whoever can survive the night's pranks and scares will win Belson's old Acedia game system!

added.title: All Aboard the Space Train
added.description: In a strange turn of events, the JLA enlist the help of Space Cabbie and Jonah Hex to stop the hijacking of an intergalactic space train.

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
added.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

added.title: Mxy's Mix-Up
added.description: As the Justice League is trying to protect the United Nations from Grodd's gorilla army, Mr. Mxyptlk pops up from the fifth dimension and thinks it would be great fun to put each of the superheroes' brains into another hero's body.

added.title: Booster's Gold
added.description: Green Arrow becomes involved with Booster Gold when he discovers that the self-centered superhero has brought dinosaurs back from the past for a money-making venture.

added.title: Dust Buddies
added.description: As punishment for making a huge mess in their house, Belson's mom makes Belson clean up, offering their usual maid service to Mary and Clarence. Embarrassed of their messy house, Mary and Clarence hurry to clean up before the maid arrives.

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: Chalmers Santiago
added.description: While Clarence spends a lazy Saturday playing 8-bit adventure game Dragon's Cusp, Mary asks him to return some mail to the guy across the street Chalmers Santiago, whom they've never seen. Clarence makes it his mission to befriend the mysterious neighbor, only to find out it's someone he knows quite well.

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Balance
added.description: Ms. Baker introduces a new student, a short little kid with a hook for a hand named Balance. Clarence is pumped to have a new friend, despite Balance's gruff attitude and snarky jibes at the other kids. When Clarence discovers a disturbing secret about Balance, he and Belson team up to expose him for who he truly is.

added.title: Cough It Up
added.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Subterranean Homesick Blues/Honey Struck
added.description: Subterranean Homesick Blues: The AO return home to learn that no time has passed but they soon discover their knowledge of brawling has gotten years more advanced./Honey Struck: After Strata is sent packing the AO discover that they have picked up a hitchhiker a Panda-like Bakugan who is nothing but sticky trouble.

added.title: Shun Shine/Ronin Son
added.description: Shun Shine: The AO want to evolve their Bakugan like Dan did with Drago but only Shun finds a way by tapping into the energy of the Mind Core Cell./Ronin Son: When Shun's cousin Masato Kazami claims Hydorous as his intellectual property the AO must battle to keep their friend by their side.

added.title: More More More!
added.description: In order to out-muscle Guts Man, Mega Man copies the big bot's schematics, and his insatiable appetite!

added.title: Blast Resort
added.description: Mega Man must assist Blasto Woman in a heist to stop a powerful EMP emitter from falling into the wrong hands.

added.title: Too Much Is Never Enough
added.description: Envious of Namagem's ability to wield more than three powers at a time, Mega Man tries taking all of his replicated schematics on board, with grave side effects.

added.title: The Bluster Bunch
added.description: A trail of tornadic destruction leads Mega Man, Suna, and Rush through a series of encounters with Air Man's quirky siblings.

added.title: It's Chemistry, Man
added.description: Chemistry Man lays siege to Silicon Central when he discovers that his replacement, Miss CHO, has been presented with a teaching award.

added.title: The Hands of Time
added.description: Master Wu mistakenly tries to single-handedly complete a battle he began decades ago against Acronix, one of the twin Hands of Time. But the arrival of the first Time Blade, a weapon with the power to speed up time, sends the Ninja to the Monastery just in time to rescue their master from certain doom.

added.title: The Hatching
added.description: The Ninja learn more about the Krux and Acronix, the two fallen Elemental Masters known as the Hands of Time, and are sure this threat has finally been eliminated. But with Wu out of action and suffering from the effects of the Time Punch, the Ninja discover a new enemy in their midst, the Vermillion Warriors. And the Ninjas have no idea who controls them.

added.title: A Time of Traitors
added.description: Kai's investigation of a Vermillion Warrior Helmet leads him to discover Krux is alive and well in NinjaGo, living under an assumed identity. Meanwhile, as the Vermillion Warriors go on a kidnapping spree, Lloyd struggles with his role as master-in-training and Nya does her best to reboot Zane, who was knocked off line in his first battle with the Vermillion.

added.title: Scavengers
added.description: In the midst of an epidemic of mysterious metal thefts by the Vermillion Warriors, Lloyd realizes stepping up and taking over for the ailing Master Wu is not an easy task.

added.title: A Line in the Sand
added.description: While the Ninja fight to save MegaMonster Amusement Park, Jay struggles to defend his family's home from the Vermillion Warriors. But the arrival of the Emerald Time Blade, with its ability to slow time, leads to a desert chase as the heroes try to reach the Blade before the snakes get it!

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: Goose Chase
added.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

added.title: Reeking Havoc/Live & Let Dynamo
added.description: Reeking Havoc: This year, the Professor's submission for the 2nd Annual Townsville Chili Cookoff is X-tra special. But this X-tra special ingredient doesn't settle well with Townsville's tummies./Live and Let Dynamo: Dynamo is terrorizing Townsville but who's working the controls? Now, the girls have to battle their own robot while trying to discover who is trying to pit their own weapon against them.

added.title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
added.description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
added.description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

added.title: Save Mojo/Substitute Creature
added.description: Save Mojo: An animal activist group sets out to protect Mojo, ensuring that he can behave like the naturally evil monkey that he is./Substitute Creature: A substitute teacher comes to Pokey Oaks and the girls are sure that this creature teacher is up to no good.

added.title: Telephonies/Tough Love
added.description: Telephonies: The Gangreen Gang gets hold of the Powerpuff Girls' Hotline and makes crank calls sending the Powerpuff Girls on a wild goose chases all over town./Tough Love: Everyone in Townsville loves the Powerpuff Girls! But the citizens have a sudden change of heart when Him sends out an evil gas turning the entire town against their favorite superheroes.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Helter Shelter/Power Lunch
added.description: Helter Shelter: Bubbles has a habit of saving helpless animals and the Professor is sick of it. When Bubbles brings a baby whale home, she and her sisters have a whale of a time hiding this new addition./Power Lunch: The Gangreen Gang shoplifts from a mini-mart, shoveling loads of food down their throats as fast as possible. When the girls fire at them with their laser vision, a strange reaction occurs.

added.title: Gettin' Twiggy with It/Cop Out
added.description: Getting' Twiggy with It: Mitch takes Twiggy, the class hamster, home for the weekend. But when Mitch flushes Twiggy down the toilet, he emerges bigger and badder than ever./Cop Out: A lazy Townsville cop gets fired and blames the girls for saving the day too often, thereby stealing his job. Now, it's payback time and he has the perfect plan to stop those pint-size punks.

added.title: The Bubbles-Sitters Club
added.description: Bubbles tries to prove that she's responsible enough to own a dog.

added.title: Memory Lane of Pain
added.description: While going through the Professor's scrapbook, Bubbles starts to question if she's ever been a hero.

added.title: Breaking Bliss
added.description: When Bliss struggles to control her powers an evil force arises to take advantage.

added.title: You're a Good Man, Mojo Jojo
added.description: The holidays are Mojo's favorite time…for ruining everything! But this year, he may just learn the reason for the season.

added.title: Derby Dollies
added.description: When Bubbles joins the Derbytantes, Buttercup finds herself on the sidelines.

added.title: The Blossom Files
added.description: Blossom's skepticism is put to the test when she believes she's encountered a space alien.

added.title: Horn, Sweet Horn
added.description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

added.title: Bye Bye, Bellum
added.description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: Professor Proofed
added.description: After the Professor's latest experiment goes awry, the girls become overprotective.

added.title: Team of Broccoli
added.description: The Warrior Family's broccoli crop is stolen and the Warriors and Danelda team up to track it down underground.

added.title: The Ballad of Sailor Sidney
added.description: A Warrior mission to find missing Sailor Sidney for the Keelhaul Cove Pirates.

added.title: Potion in the Ocean
added.description: Witchy Simone joins the Warriors on a mission deep in the Fickle Sea to find an eye of newt for her magic potion, but Man Fish the Fish Man won't let them harm his sea newt pal!

added.title: Share and Share Dislike
added.description: Super Shooting Star Magisword is the coolest Magisword ever, but Vambre and Prohyas can't seem to share it, and even a quest to reclaim the never-melting ice cube back from Frosteratu can't shake their obsession.

added.title: Sibling Sorcery
added.description: When Phil the Pilferer steals the Golden Broomstick Magisword Award intended for Witchy Simone's famous younger sister, Witchy Sparkles, the Warriors lead the search in getting it back.

added.title: Too Young
added.description: Princess Bubblegum's uncle attempts to usurp Ooo's throne.

added.title: The Monster
added.description: Lumpy Space Princess's parents have come to ask Finn and Jake to find their daughter and convince her to come home.

added.title: What Was Missing
added.description: Finn & Jake do battle with a powerful door lord.

added.title: Thank You
added.description: The Snow Golem and his beseeching pup pay a visit to the Fire Kingdom.

added.title: It Came From the Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: The Other Tarts
added.description: Finn and Jake volunteer for a dangerous assignment: currying rare tarts for a meeting of Ooo royalty.

added.title: Death in Bloom
added.description: Finn and Jake are terrible house sitters and have to go on a quest to replace Princess Bubblegum's rare flower.

added.title: Enchiridion
added.description: Finn quests for a book that will make him a better hero.

added.title: Evicted!
added.description: Marceline shows up and informs that the tree fort was once hers and she wants it back.

added.title: Ocean of Fear
added.description: Finn faces his biggest challenge yet, overcoming his fear of water.

added.title: The Visitor Part 2
added.description: Dino-Mode Grimlock careens out-of-control around the Ark after drinking Wheeljack's hyper-fuel.

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 1
added.description: The Decepticons compete to be the first to bring Megatron Optimus Prime's spark while Hot Rod chases the "Moon Cheetah."

added.title: Bring Me the Spark of Optimus Prime Part 2
added.description: Slipstream searches for her missing Seekers while Hot Rod's "Moon Cheetah" chase brings him unexpectedly aboard the Nemesis.

added.title: Divided We Stand
added.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
added.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

added.title: Rook Tales
added.description: Rook's former teacher will preserve Revonnahgander traditions at any cost.

added.title: The Color of Monkey
added.description: Everybody's favorite alien conman, Argit, takes on a shady sidekick, Simian, in a shocking new business.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
From Hedorium to Eternity
added.description: 11-year-old Ben, Gwen, and friends go on the adventure of a lifetime in their own backyard.

added.title: Let's Do the Time War Again
added.description: Ben, Skurd and Rook find themselves caught in an endless time loop as enemies from the future converge on Bellwood.

added.title: Third Time's a Charm
added.description: Charmaster returns to exact her revenge on Gwendolyn once and for all.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: Power Outage
added.description: A ghoul known as Calythos possesses the Parasite in order to drain the Justice League of its powers and use that stolen strength to open a massive volcano.

added.title: Las manecillas del tiempo
added.description: El maestro Wu intenta completar una batalla que comenzó hace décadas contra Acronix.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: La incubacion
added.description: Los Ninja descubren un nuevo enemigo en medio de ellos.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Una epoca de traidores
added.description: Lloyd lucha con su papel como maestro en entrenamiento y Nya hace todo lo posible para reiniciar a Zane.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Carroneros
added.description: Lloyd se da cuenta de que hacerse cargo del debilitado Maestro Wu no es una tarea fácil.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Una linea en la arena
added.description: Jay lucha por defender la casa de su familia.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El vagon inacabado
added.description: El grupo entra a un vagón sin terminar e intenta arreglarlo.

added.title: El vagon cromado
added.description: El grupo se encuentra con una cara familiar en un vagón espejado.

added.title: El vagon de la piscina de pelotas
added.description: El grupo es confrontado por una nueva y extraña fuerza en una aventura por un vagón lleno de pelotas.

added.title: El vagon del pasado
added.description: Tulip se arriesga al confiar en un viejo enemigo.

added.title: La locomotora
added.description: Tulip logra llegar al frente del tren y debe afrontar una decisión.

added.title: Intolerancia Heladil
added.description: Los campistas obtienen poderes mágicos gracias a la reserva de helado mágico de las brujas.

added.title: La Desaparicion de la Manta de Peper
added.description: La manta de Pepper desaparece en una pijamada en la cabaña.

added.title: Erizo Nina Lobo
added.description: A Hedgehog lo muerde un perrito tierno y comienza a comportarse de manera extraña.

added.title: Mister Softbol
added.description: Susie desafía a los campistas a jugar un partido de softball para librarse de una tarea.

added.title: Peludos Bebes Rosas del Tiempo
added.description: Oscar y Erizo aprenden a detener el tiempo.

added.title: Una extrana conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Hogar, dulce hogar
added.description: Los Fantásticos vuelven a casa y se dan cuenta de que el tiempo no ha pasado. Pronto descubren que su conocimiento acerca de las batallas ha aumentado de forma exponencial.

added.title: Un golpe de ternura
added.description: Después de derrotar a Strata, Los Fantásticos se dan cuenta de que no volvieron solos, sino con un Bakugan parecido a un panda que les dará muchos problemas.

added.title: El hijo prodigo
added.description: Mientras los Fantásticos intentan evolucionar a sus Bakugan como lo hizo Dan con Drago, el primo de Shun, Masato, llega a la ciudad para llevarlo de regreso a Japón.

added.title: El poder interior
added.description: Masato Kazami vuelve junto con los guardaespaldas de la familia para llevar a Shun a Japón, pero esta vez, Shun y Hydorous tienen una sorpresa preparada.

added.title: El baul de los recuerdos
added.description: Al ser confrontada por China Riot, Lia logra evolucionar a Pegatrix cuando comprende la verdadera razón de su obsesión por las cámaras.

added.title: Malos actores
added.description: Alguien expone a Dan por mentir acerca de la evolución de Drago, mientras el equipo se enfrenta a Duran Dane y su desdichado Bakugan, Nillious.

added.title: El atrapador
added.description: Dan y Wynton se encuentran con la posible ubicación secreta de la Célula Núcleo, y con el coronel Tripp, que busca apoderarse de la fuente de energía.

added.title: La sed de poder
added.description: Tras una discusión entre Wynton y Dan, el coronel Tripp controla la mente de Wynton para que ataque la ciudad con Lupitheon. Esto inicia una guerra entre Los Fantásticos y el ejército.

added.title: Uncle Greedpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in need of some extra cash, so he starts charging for his services.

added.title: Tongue Tied
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a shy kid gain confidence.

added.title: The Phone Call
added.description: A threatening phone call from a stranger causes the gang to panic.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: G'day Mornin'
added.description: Uncle grandpa goes to Australia where he must stop an out-of-control collecting kangaroo before he destroys the Earth.

added.title: Fear of Flying
added.description: Uncle grandpa helps a young boy overcome his fear of flying.

added.title: Fool Moon
added.description: Strange things start happening when Uncle Grandpa installs a moon roof in the RV.

added.title: Mustache Tree
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa runs out of mustaches, he travels to the mustache tree to stock up. But upon arrival, it seems a new clan of elves have become very territorial over the tree. Now, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must fight in order to obtain a new 'stache.

added.title: Wasteland
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa neglects his garbage duties, he embarks on a quest to save his friends from the overflowing pile of trash.

added.title: Duck Lips
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa molds her mouth into duck lips, a young girl must face the consequences of her new found popularity.

removed.title: Aspirations
removed.description: The Gangreen Gang is actually committing brilliant crimes. But behind every great gang, there has to be a great woman.

removed.title: I See a Funny Cartoon in Your Future/Octi-Gone
removed.description: I See a Funny Cartoon In Your Future: The girls have the rare task of fighting a medium who is committing petty thefts./Octi-gone: When Bubbles finds a single leg of Octi's, she sets out to find out who took her toy and what they want from her.

removed.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

removed.description: That's Not My Baby!: The girls save a baby from a monster attacking Townsville but can't find the mother. removed.title: Radio Silence
removed.description: Oscar must get Hedgehog a special sandwich in order to save their friendship.
